y%20have%20more%20money%20coming%20in.%20And%20it's%20clear%20that%20income%20growth%20is%20easing%20as%20the%20labor%20markets%20cool.%20The%20percentage%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fraises-promotions-harder-get-low-quit-rates-interest-rates-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20quitting%20their%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20hit%20fresh%20lows%20at%20the%20end%20of%202024%2C%20and%20as%20quits%20decline%2C%20so%20too%20does%20wage%20growth.%20This%20makes%20sense%3A%20When%20workers%20are%20less%20likely%20to%20leave%20their%20jobs%2C%20employers%20feel%20less%20need%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpromotions-salaries-cut-career-advancement-stagnation-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Egive%20them%20raises%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20keep%20them%20around%2C%20which%20shifts%20power%20from%20employees%20to%20employers.%20And%20as%20incomes%20slow%2C%20so%20will%20consumption.%20In%20fact%2C%20we've%20already%20seen%20some%20of%20this%20decline%3A%20Inflation-adjusted%20incomes%20net%20of%20transfer%20payments%20%E2%80%94%20a%20proxy%20for%20people's%20paychecks%20with%20government%20payments%20like%20Social%20Security%20and%20Medicaid%20stripped%20out%20%E2%80%94%20was%20a%20full%20percentage%20point%20below%20the%20pace%20of%20consumption.%20At%20the%20same%20time%2C%20the%20personal%20savings%20rate%20(a%20measure%20of%20the%20percentage%20that%20people%20are%20setting%20aside)%20fell%20to%203.8%25%20from%204.4%25%20in%202023%2C%20suggesting%20that%20Americans%20were%20dipping%20into%20their%20reserves%20to%20keep%20the%20spending%20going.%20But%20there's%20a%20limit%20to%20how%20much%20consumers%20can%20draw%20down%20their%20savings%20to%20fuel%20buying.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FPxhTn%2F1%2F%5