%20but%20provided%20no%20reason%20for%20the%20decision%20in%20the%20ruling.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThis%20stay%20gives%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20time%20to%20evaluate%20the%20case%20and%20decide%20whether%20the%20Trump%20administration%20must%20release%20funds.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20issued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F25546064-24a831-order%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20ruling%20on%20Wednesday%20night%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20halted%20a%20lower%20court's%20order%20for%20President%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EDonald%20Trump%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20release%20funding%20for%20the%20US%20Agency%20for%20International%20Development.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20February%2026%20ruling%2C%20the%20SCOTUS%20blocked%20a%20court%20order%20from%20District%20Judge%20Amir%20Ali%20related%20to%20two%20cases%20brought%20against%20the%20Trump%20administration%20by%20aid%20organizations%20including%20the%20AIDS%20Vaccine%20Advocacy%20Coalition%20and%20the%20Global%20Health%20Council.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAli's%20ruling%20on%20the%20cases%20would%20have%20compelled%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20release%20foreign%20aid%20dollars%20to%20grant%20recipients%20and%20USAID%20contractors%20by%20midnight%20on%20Wednesday.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20SCOTUS%20halted%20Ali's%20decision%20after%20attorneys%20for%20the%20Trump%20administration%20on%20Wednesday%20said%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fecf.dcd.uscourts.gov%2Fcgi-bin%2Fshow_temp.pl%3Ffile%3D9395601-0--85430.pdf%26type%3Dapplication%2Fpdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecourt%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ethat%20Secretary%20of%20State%20Marco%20Rubio%20has%20already%20%26quot%3Bmade%20a%20final%20decision%26quot%3B%20on%20what%20organizations%20to%20award%20funds%20to.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESarah%20Harris%2C%20the%20acting%20solicitor%20general%2C%20appealed%20to%20the%20SCOTUS%20on%20Wednesday%20to%20vacate%20the%20lower%20court's%20order.%20In%20her%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.supremecourt.gov%2FDocketPDF%2F24%2F24A831%2F348801%2F20250226200602007_AIDS_Vaccine_Advocacy_Coalition_et_al_application.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efiling%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Harris%20said%20that%20the%20%26quot%3Bdistrict%20court's%20imminent%20and%20arbitrary%20deadline%20makes%20full%20compliance%20impossible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHarris%20added%20that%20the%20lower%20court's%20order%20required%20the%20administration%20to%20disburse%20%26quot%3Bnearly%20%242%20billion%20by%2011%3A59%20p.m.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20payments%20cannot%20be%20accomplished%20in%20the%20time%20allotted%20by%20the%20Court%20and%20would%20instead%20take%20multiple%20weeks%2C%26quot%3B%20Harris%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20John%20Roberts%20granted%20the%20administrative%20stay%20but%20provided%20no%20reason%20for%20the%20decision%20in%20the%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Eruling.%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3ERoberts%20has%20given%20the%20plaintiffs%20who%20sued%20the%20administration%20until%20Friday%20to%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20SCOTUS'%20stay%20now%20gives%20the%20court%20time%20to%20evaluate%20and%20rule%20on%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20request.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUSAID%20was%20one%20of%20the%20first%20targets%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffederal-agencies-musk-doge-targeted-list-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDepartment%20of%20Government%20Efficiency%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20cuts%20to%20USAID%20come%20after%20Trump%2C%20in%20a%20January%2020%20executive%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.federalregister.gov%2Fdocuments%2F2025%2F01%2F30%2F2025-02091%2Freevaluating-and-realigning-united-states-foreign-aid%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3Eorder%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20called%20for%20a%2090-day%20freeze%20on%20foreign%20aid.%20That%20executive%20order%20and%20other%20actions%20have%20affected%20thousands%20of%20US%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJudges%20other%20than%20Ali%20have%20made%20rulings%20that%20slowed%20the%20Trump%20team's%20attempts%20to%20dismantle%20USAID.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20February%207%2C%20Judge%20Carl%20Nichols%20issued%20a%20temporary%20restraining%20order%20that%20paused%20the%20administration's%20USAID%20staff%20reductions.%20But%20USAID%20suffered%20a%20major%20court%20loss%20on%20February%2021%20when%20Nichols%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjudge-allows-trump-usaid-reductions-proceed-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eallowed%20headcount%20cuts%20to%20go%20ahead%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20reversing%20his%20previous%20order.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20USAID%20distributed%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-usaid-ukraine-middle-east-foreign-aid-aids-vaccinations-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eclose%20to%20%2432.5%20billion%20in%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20primarily%20to%20causes%20in%20Africa%20and%20the%20Middle%20East.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscotus-block-lower-courts-order-trump-release-usaid-funds-2025-2%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1740631320000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67bfe9ea69253ccddf97ba82%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscotus-block-lower-courts-order-trump-release-usaid-funds-2025-2%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20SCOTUS%20ruling%20blocks%20a%20court%20order%20that%20compelled%20the%20Trump%20administration%20to%20release%20funding%20to%20USAID%20by%20midnight%20on%20Wednesday.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Cheryl%20Teh)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A76%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.