n%20infected%20person%20can%20be%20contagious%20without%20knowing%20it%20for%20up%20to%20four%20days%2C%20Anton%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20people%20register%20their%20children%20for%20school%20in%20kindergarten%20through%20seventh%20grade%2C%20they%20provide%20updates%20to%20us%20and%20the%20school%20districts%20on%20the%20vaccination%20coverage%20in%20their%20district%2C%26quot%3B%20Anton%20said.%20%26quot%3BGenerally%20the%20coverage%20level%20statewide%20has%20dipped%20down%20in%20recent%20years.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMeasles%20death%20is%20uncommon.%20The%20last%20reported%20measles%20death%20of%20an%20adult%20in%20the%20US%20occurred%20in%202015%20when%20a%20Washington%20woman%20contracted%20it%20at%20a%20health%20clinic%2C%20CDC%20data%20shows.%20Anton%20said%20a%20child%20also%20died%20of%20measles%20in%20Texas%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frfk-jr-confirmed-health-secretary-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ERobert%20F.%20Kennedy%20Jr.%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20vaccine%20critic%2C%20was%20confirmed%20as%20US%20Health%20Secretary%20this%20month%20despite%20opposition%20from%20medical%20professionals%20and%20some%20members%20of%20Congress.%20He%20has%2C%20however%2C%20pledged%20to%20maintain%20existing%20vaccination%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20are%20following%20the%20measles%20epidemic%20every%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20Kennedy%20said%20during%20a%20meeting%20with%20President%20Donald%20Trump's%20cabinet%20at%20the%20White%20House.%20%26quot%3BIncidentally%2C%20there%20have%20been%20four%20measles%20outbreaks%20this%20year.%20In%20this%20country%20last%20year%20there%20were%2016.%20So%2C%20it's%20not%20unusual.%20We%20have%20measles%20outbreaks%20every%20year.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20mentioned%20that%20two%20people%20had%20died%20in%20the%20outbreak%2C%20but%20the%20Texas%20DSHS%20was%20only%20able%20to%20confirm%20one%20death%20so%20far.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%2